  name              = "example"
  budget_type       = "USAGE"
  limit_amount      = "10.0"
  limit_unit        = "dollars"
  time_period_start = "2006-01-02_15:04"
  time_unit         = "MONTHLY"
}
```

### Resource: aws_budgets_budget_action > Argument Reference > Definition

Source: https://github.com/hashicorp/terraform-provider-aws/blob/v6.33.0/website/docs/r/budgets_budget_action.html.markdown

The definition block specifies type-specific parameters for the budget action and supports three action types: iam_action_definition for applying IAM policies to users, groups, or roles; ssm_action_definition for running AWS Systems Manager documents; and scp_action_definition for applying service control policies. The structure of the definition block varies based on the action_type selected, allowing different cost control mechanisms to be implemented through a unified resource.

